'''''Boba Fett: Bounty on Bar-Kooda''''' is the first issue in the [[Star Wars: Boba Fett (comic series)|Boba Fett]] series of one-shot comic books. It was written by [[John Wagner]] and illustrated by [[Cam Kennedy]]. It was released on [[December 5]], [[1995]] by [[Dark Horse Comics]].

==Publisher's summary==
''He is the one man who delivered Han Solo to both Darth Vader and Jabba the Hutt. Across the galaxy, the most-wanted criminals shudder at the mere mention of his name&hellip; Boba Fett!''

''Following the events of ''Star Wars: Dark Empire II'', a Hutt's misguided affections lead to a death contract on a faraway planet. Hired by the Hutt, Boba Fett pursues an intergalactic magician who may hold the key to the Hutt's future. The fact that the magician has died only poses a slight problem for the bounty hunter, as not even the dead can escape from Boba Fett!''

==Plot summary==
{{Plot|comic}}

==Continuity==
Although the publisher's summary for ''Boba Fett: Bounty on Bar-Kooda'', as well as the article "[[ComicScan|Pulp Faction]]" in the [[Star Wars Galaxy Magazine 6|sixth issue]] of the ''[[Star Wars Galaxy Magazine]]'' both indicate that the events of the comic issue take place after those of ''[[Star Wars: Dark Empire II]]'',<ref name="PulpFaction">{{GalaxyCite|6|ComicScan|ComicScan: Pulp Faction}}</ref> ''[[The New Essential Guide to Characters]]''<ref name="NEGTC">''[[The New Essential Guide to Characters]]''</ref> and the [[The Official Star Wars Fact File 97|ninety-seventh issue]] of ''[[The Official Star Wars Fact File]]'' both imply that they, in fact, occurred before the events of that series.<ref name="FF97">{{FactFile|97|FET 29-32|Boba Fett}}</ref> ''[[Star Wars: The Comics Companion]]'', which generally organizes the comic stories described within in [[in-universe]] chronological order, places ''Bounty on Bar-Kooda'', dated to "ten years after ''A New Hope''," after ''Dark Empire II'' ("ten years after ''A New Hope''") but also between the ''[[Star Wars: Empire's End]]'' and ''[[Crimson Empire]]'' series (both "eleven years after ''A New Hope''").<ref name="ComicsCompanion">''[[Star Wars: The Comics Companion]]''</ref>

